ssh-alertd (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Run as a dedicated "ssh-alertd" system user (sysusers.d) instead of
    DynamicUser, and grant it ownership of the config (tmpfiles.d) so the
    daemon can read its token. Fixes a startup failure with permission denied
    on /etc/ssh-alertd/config.json.

